[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6661,
        "end_time": 9885,
        "text": "Light: it&#39;s the fastest thing in the universe,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 9885,
        "end_time": 12066,
        "text": "but we can still measure its speed"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 12066,
        "end_time": 13895,
        "text": "if we slow down the animation,"
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 13895,
        "end_time": 15805,
        "text": "we can analyze light&#39;s motion using"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 15805,
        "end_time": 17739,
        "text": "a space-time diagram,"
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 17739,
        "end_time": 19839,
        "text": "which takes a flipbook of animation panels,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 19839,
        "end_time": 21973,
        "text": "and turns them on their side."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 21973,
        "end_time": 25080,
        "text": "In this lesson, we&#39;ll add the single experimental fact"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 25080,
        "end_time": 27977,
        "text": "that whenever anyone measures just how fast light moves,"
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 27977,
        "end_time": 29329,
        "text": "they get the same answer:"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 29329,
        "end_time": 33281,
        "text": "299,792,458 meters every second,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 33281,
        "end_time": 35710,
        "text": "which means that when we draw light"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 35710,
        "end_time": 36882,
        "text": "on our space-time diagram,"
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 36882,
        "end_time": 39991,
        "text": "it&#39;s world line always has to appear at the same angle."
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 39991,
        "end_time": 42354,
        "text": "But we saw previously that speed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 42354,
        "end_time": 44843,
        "text": "or equivalently world line angles,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 44843,
        "end_time": 47502,
        "text": "change when we look at things from"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 47502,
        "end_time": 49249,
        "text": "other people&#39;s perspective."
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 49249,
        "end_time": 51804,
        "text": "To explore this contradiction,"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 51804,
        "end_time": 53900,
        "text": "let&#39;s see what happens if I start moving"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 53900,
        "end_time": 57988,
        "text": "while I stand still and shine the laser at Tom."
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 57988,
        "end_time": 60455,
        "text": "First, we&#39;ll need to construct the space-time diagram."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 60455,
        "end_time": 61875,
        "text": "Yes, that means taking all of"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 61875,
        "end_time": 64284,
        "text": "the different panels showing the different moments in time"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 64284,
        "end_time": 66289,
        "text": "and stacking them up."
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 66289,
        "end_time": 68338,
        "text": "From the side, we see the world line"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 68338,
        "end_time": 71548,
        "text": "of the laser light at its correct fixed angle,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 71548,
        "end_time": 72660,
        "text": "just as before."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 72660,
        "end_time": 74213,
        "text": "So far, so good."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 74213,
        "end_time": 77634,
        "text": "But that space-time diagram represents Andrew&#39;s perspective."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 77634,
        "end_time": 79454,
        "text": "What does it look like to me?"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 79454,
        "end_time": 81246,
        "text": "In the last lesson, we showed"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 81246,
        "end_time": 84516,
        "text": "how to get Tom&#39;s perspective moving all the panels"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 84516,
        "end_time": 88351,
        "text": "along a bit until his world line is completely vertical."
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 88351,
        "end_time": 91825,
        "text": "But look carefully at the light world line."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 91825,
        "end_time": 93222,
        "text": "The rearrangement of the panels"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 93222,
        "end_time": 95714,
        "text": "means it&#39;s now tilted over too far."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 95714,
        "end_time": 98883,
        "text": "I&#39;d measure light traveling faster than Andrew would."
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 98883,
        "end_time": 100855,
        "text": "But every experiment we&#39;ve ever done,"
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 100855,
        "end_time": 102405,
        "text": "and we&#39;ve tried very hard,"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 102405,
        "end_time": 106708,
        "text": "says that everyone measures light to have a fixed speed."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 106708,
        "end_time": 108052,
        "text": "So let&#39;s start again."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 108052,
        "end_time": 111642,
        "text": "In the 1900s, a clever chap named Albert Einstein"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 111642,
        "end_time": 114487,
        "text": "worked out how to see things properly,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 114487,
        "end_time": 116147,
        "text": "from Tom&#39;s point of view,"
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 116147,
        "end_time": 119442,
        "text": "while still getting the speed of light right."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 119442,
        "end_time": 122867,
        "text": "First, we need to glue together the separate panels"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 122867,
        "end_time": 125248,
        "text": "into one solid block."
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 125248,
        "end_time": 127069,
        "text": "This gives us our space-time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 127069,
        "end_time": 128946,
        "text": "turning space and time into"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 128946,
        "end_time": 132277,
        "text": "one smooth, continuous material."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 132277,
        "end_time": 134723,
        "text": "And now, here is the trick."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 134723,
        "end_time": 138076,
        "text": "What you do is stretch your block of space-time"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 138076,
        "end_time": 140423,
        "text": "along the light world line,"
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 140423,
        "end_time": 142950,
        "text": "then squash it by the same amount,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 142950,
        "end_time": 144926,
        "text": "but at right angles to the light world line,"
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 144926,
        "end_time": 147220,
        "text": "and abracadabra!"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 147220,
        "end_time": 149286,
        "text": "Tom&#39;s world line has gone vertical,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 149286,
        "end_time": 152775,
        "text": "so this does represent the world from his point of view,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 152775,
        "end_time": 154453,
        "text": "but most importantly,"
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 154453,
        "end_time": 157822,
        "text": "the light world line has never changed its angle,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 157822,
        "end_time": 160331,
        "text": "and so light will be measured by Tom"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 160331,
        "end_time": 162957,
        "text": "going at the correct speed."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 162957,
        "end_time": 164780,
        "text": "This superb trick is known as"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 164780,
        "end_time": 168005,
        "text": "a Lorentz transformation."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 168005,
        "end_time": 169490,
        "text": "Yeah, more than a trick."
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 169490,
        "end_time": 171024,
        "text": "Slice up the space-time into"
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 171024,
        "end_time": 172353,
        "text": "new panels and you have"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 172353,
        "end_time": 175043,
        "text": "the physically correct animation."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 175043,
        "end_time": 176373,
        "text": "I&#39;m stationary in the car,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 176373,
        "end_time": 178304,
        "text": "everything else is coming past me"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 178304,
        "end_time": 179934,
        "text": "and the speed of light"
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 179934,
        "end_time": 182392,
        "text": "works out to be that same fixed value"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 182392,
        "end_time": 184177,
        "text": "that we know everyone measures."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 184177,
        "end_time": 185403,
        "text": "On the other hand,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 185403,
        "end_time": 186929,
        "text": "something strange has happened."
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 186929,
        "end_time": 190873,
        "text": "The fence posts aren&#39;t spaced a meter apart anymore,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 190873,
        "end_time": 192384,
        "text": "and my mom will be worried"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 192384,
        "end_time": 194520,
        "text": "that I look a bit thin."
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 194520,
        "end_time": 197791,
        "text": "But that&#39;s not fair. Why don&#39;t I get to look thin?"
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 197791,
        "end_time": 199834,
        "text": "I thought physics was supposed to be the same"
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 199834,
        "end_time": 200937,
        "text": "for everyone."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 200937,
        "end_time": 203052,
        "text": "Yes, no, it is, and you do."
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 203052,
        "end_time": 204862,
        "text": "All that stretching and squashing"
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 204862,
        "end_time": 206841,
        "text": "of space-time has just muddled together"
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 206841,
        "end_time": 208977,
        "text": "what we used to think of separately"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 208977,
        "end_time": 210791,
        "text": "as space and time."
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 210791,
        "end_time": 212702,
        "text": "This particular squashing effect"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 212702,
        "end_time": 215251,
        "text": "is known as Lorentz contraction."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 215251,
        "end_time": 216728,
        "text": "Okay, but I still don&#39;t look thin."
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 216728,
        "end_time": 218160,
        "text": "No, yes, you do."
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 218160,
        "end_time": 220348,
        "text": "Now that we know better about space-time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 220348,
        "end_time": 221484,
        "text": "we should redraw"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 221484,
        "end_time": 223650,
        "text": "what the scene looked like to me."
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 223650,
        "end_time": 226992,
        "text": "To you, I appear Lorentz contracted."
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 226992,
        "end_time": 229760,
        "text": "Oh but to you, I appear Lorentz contracted."
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 229760,
        "end_time": 230845,
        "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 230845,
        "end_time": 233344,
        "text": "Uh, well, at least it&#39;s fair."
    },
    {
        "index": 99,
        "start_time": 233344,
        "end_time": 234755,
        "text": "And speaking of fairness,"
    },
    {
        "index": 100,
        "start_time": 234755,
        "end_time": 236899,
        "text": "just as space gets muddled with time,"
    },
    {
        "index": 101,
        "start_time": 236899,
        "end_time": 239442,
        "text": "time also gets muddled with space,"
    },
    {
        "index": 102,
        "start_time": 239442,
        "end_time": 242029,
        "text": "in an effect known as time dilation."
    },
    {
        "index": 103,
        "start_time": 242029,
        "end_time": 243417,
        "text": "No, at everyday speeds,"
    },
    {
        "index": 104,
        "start_time": 243417,
        "end_time": 245260,
        "text": "such as Tom&#39;s car reaches,"
    },
    {
        "index": 105,
        "start_time": 245260,
        "end_time": 248402,
        "text": "actually all the effects are much, much smaller"
    },
    {
        "index": 106,
        "start_time": 248402,
        "end_time": 249854,
        "text": "than we&#39;ve illustrated them."
    },
    {
        "index": 107,
        "start_time": 249854,
        "end_time": 253252,
        "text": "Oh, yet, careful experiments,"
    },
    {
        "index": 108,
        "start_time": 253252,
        "end_time": 255641,
        "text": "for instance watching the behavior of tiny particles"
    },
    {
        "index": 109,
        "start_time": 255641,
        "end_time": 257613,
        "text": "whizzing around the Large Hadron Collider"
    },
    {
        "index": 110,
        "start_time": 257613,
        "end_time": 259972,
        "text": "confirmed that the effects are real."
    },
    {
        "index": 111,
        "start_time": 259972,
        "end_time": 261008,
        "text": "And now that space-time is"
    },
    {
        "index": 112,
        "start_time": 261008,
        "end_time": 263640,
        "text": "an experimentally confirmed part of reality,"
    },
    {
        "index": 113,
        "start_time": 263640,
        "end_time": 265743,
        "text": "we can get a bit more ambitious."
    },
    {
        "index": 114,
        "start_time": 265743,
        "end_time": 267475,
        "text": "What if we were to start playing"
    },
    {
        "index": 115,
        "start_time": 267475,
        "end_time": 271494,
        "text": "with the material of space-time itself?"
    },
    {
        "index": 116,
        "start_time": 271494,
        "end_time": 274756,
        "text": "We&#39;ll find out all about that in the next animation."
    }
]